# UI: Preventing Text Wrapping

**Goal**: Ensure UI elements (badges, links, buttons) don't break across lines unexpectedly.

## Problem

Text in badges, links, and buttons can wrap to multiple lines, breaking layout and readability.

## Solution: `whitespace-nowrap`

### Badges

```tsx
<span className={`px-3 py-1.5 rounded-md text-sm font-bold whitespace-nowrap ${statusColor}`}>
  {status.replace("_", " ").toUpperCase()}
</span>
```

### Links

```tsx
<Link
  href="/workflows/123"
  className="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 whitespace-nowrap"
>
  View Details →
</Link>
```

### Buttons with Icons

```tsx
<Button className="whitespace-nowrap">
  <Icon className="w-4 h-4 mr-2" />
  Action Text
</Button>
```

## Rules

1. **Always add `whitespace-nowrap`** to:
   - Status/phase badges
   - Navigation links
   - Button text
   - Any text that should stay on one line

2. **Use `flex-wrap` on containers** if you want items to wrap as whole units:
   ```tsx
   <div className="flex items-center gap-2 flex-wrap">
     <Badge className="whitespace-nowrap">Status</Badge>
     <Badge className="whitespace-nowrap">Phase</Badge>
   </div>
   ```

3. **Test responsive behavior** - ensure wrapping works on mobile when needed

## Common Patterns

### Badge Groups

```tsx
<div className="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3 flex-wrap">
  <span className="px-3 py-1.5 rounded-md text-sm font-bold whitespace-nowrap bg-blue-500/20">
    DISCOVERY
  </span>
  <span className="px-3 py-1.5 rounded-md text-sm font-bold whitespace-nowrap bg-green-500/20">
    IN PROGRESS
  </span>
</div>
```

### Footer Links

```tsx
<footer className="flex justify-between items-center">
  <time className="text-sm text-gray-500">Created: 2024-01-01</time>
  <Link
    href="/workflows/123"
    className="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 whitespace-nowrap"
  >
    View Details →
  </Link>
</footer>
```

## Accessibility

- `whitespace-nowrap` doesn't affect screen readers
- Ensure text is still readable if it must wrap (use `break-words` if needed)
- Test with long text to ensure layout doesn't break
